From 18fa4ce58be87c6d8511f4e336fad7a5845c59d2 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
Date: Mon, 29 Jun 2026 19:36:42 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] rgw/posix: fix inverted If-None-Match check allowing
 overwrite

If-None-Match: * means "proceed only if the object does not exist" and
is used to prevent overwriting an existing object. The posix handler
returned PRECONDITION_FAILED when the object did not exist and allowed
the write when it did, inverting the semantics and disabling overwrite
protection.

Return PRECONDITION_FAILED when the object exists.

Signed-off-by: Sun Yuechi <sunyuechi@iscas.ac.cn>
---
 src/rgw/driver/posix/rgw_sal_posix.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/rgw/driver/posix/rgw_sal_posix.cc b/src/rgw/driver/posix/rgw_sal_posix.cc
index 92710d01669..ab3310f9596 100644
--- a/src/rgw/driver/posix/rgw_sal_posix.cc
+++ b/src/rgw/driver/posix/rgw_sal_posix.cc
@@ -4577,7 +4577,7 @@ int POSIXAtomicWriter::complete(size_t accounted_size, const std::string& etag,
   if (if_nomatch) {
     if (strcmp(if_nomatch, "*") == 0) {
       // test the object is not existing
-      if (!exists) {
+      if (exists) {
 	return -ERR_PRECONDITION_FAILED;
       }
     } else {
